    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The following database is available in the PostgreSQL server. Read the description below, then write an SQL query for each question.</p>
<p><strong>Database description:</strong></p>
<div class="editor-indent" style="margin-left: 30px;">
<p>The database has three tables, <strong>worker</strong>, <strong>company</strong>, and <strong>works_for</strong>. </p>
<ul>
<li><strong>worker</strong>: stores worker details.
<ul>
<li>Attributes: name, city, supervisor. </li>
<li>name is the primary key.</li>
<li>supervisor refers to another worker in the same table.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>company</strong>: stores company details
<ul>
<li>Attributes: name, city. </li>
<li>name is the primary key.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>works_for</strong>: links workers to companies and includes salary.
<ul>
<li>Attributes: wname, cname, salary.</li>
<li>Primary key: (wname, cname).</li>
<li>wname refers to worker.name and cname refers to company.name.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Note that a worker may live in one city (for example, Glasgow) but work for a company located in another city (for example, Edinburgh). Also, each worker can work for several companies at the same time.</p>
</div>
<p><strong>Important</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use the exact attribute names shown above to get full marks.</li>
<li>Each question includes an example result. Use it to check your answer.</li>
<li>Test your queries in PostgreSQL before submitting.</li>
<li>Your queries should work for any data (not just the sample data).</li>
<li>There is no 'check' button to resubmit.</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Question 1: </strong>Retrieve the name of each worker and their supervisor's name, where the worker lives in 'Edinburgh' and works for 'Greens'. Sort the result by name using <code>ORDER BY</code>, and use <code>DISTINCT</code> to remove duplicate rows.</p>]]></text>
<file name="insert.sql" path="/" encoding="base64"></file>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>You need a join condition in addition to the other conditions.</p>]]></text>
